{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0f7a91d3-8d22-4cd1-8911-e4514a7cf575","content":"I don't have repository-specific documentation on this topic, but I can answer based on .NET MAUI knowledge:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ **Correct.** This is the standard platform-specific attached property (`Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific`) that insets your page content to respect the safe area (notch, home indicator, etc.). It's valid in .NET 10 MAUI.\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ⚠️ **Not quite right.** There is no built-in `IgnoreSafeArea` property on `Grid` or other layouts in .NET MAUI. To have a background image extend behind the safe area while keeping other content inset, the typical approach is:\n\n1. Set `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on the page (or omit it).\n2. Use an `AbsoluteLayout` or `Grid` with the image filling the full page.\n3. Apply padding manually (or use a nested layout with `UseSafeArea`) for the foreground content.\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- Safe content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**TL;DR:** `UseSafeArea` is correct; `IgnoreSafeArea` doesn't exist in MAUI — your tutorial may be referencing Xamarin.Forms or an outdated/custom approach.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"981c02f5-728f-412d-bbae-ba75641b0726","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"9431:229965:145D6A5:16BAAC4:6A066F3B"},"id":"5aee6ed6-c588-4a17-b240-99cecd6d91a6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:56:38.732Z","parentId":"871e2fba-3de6-4c6e-878d-962f30c58b05"}
